Her Majesty was joined by Prince Philip and Princess Alexandra at reception at Canada House in Trafalgar Square . 
  Her Majesty met The Calgary Highlanders, Royal Hamilton Light Infantry and Canadian Scottish Regiment to mark the bravery of the country's servicemen and women in the First World War . 
  She looked elegant in a long blue jacket which she wore over a cream and blue floral dress . 
  The Duke of Edinburgh sat for a portrait with the regiment during the event . 
  Reception was held in honour of the three Canadian regiments which the royal members individually lead as Colonels-in-Chief  . 
 